<Defs>
  <XenotypeDef>
    <defName>PaccaMechMan_MechLord</defName>
    <label>mechlord</label>
    <description>The Mechlord is the unnatural combination of a human and a Mechhive core. Their integrated persona core and mechlink subsystem gives them enhanced mental abilities and unmatched control over mechanoids. They also excel at building and working with technology. However, they are slow and sleepy, so they tend to rely on their mechanoids or their allies to do menial labor. They are also weak to EMPs.</description>
    <descriptionShort>Mechlords excel at controlling mechanoids, and are good at building and working with technology. However, they are slow and sleepy, so they often rely on their mechanoids or allies. They are also weak to EMPs.</descriptionShort>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Xenotypes/Dirtmole</iconPath>
    <inheritable>true</inheritable>
    <nameMaker>NamerPersonPaccaMechMan</nameMaker>
    <nameMakerFemale>NamerPersonPaccaMechMan</nameMakerFemale>
    <chanceToUseNameMaker>1</chanceToUseNameMaker>
    <genes>
      <!--Archite-->
      <li>Ageless</li>
      <li>ArchiteMetabolism</li>
      <li>DiseaseFree</li> <!--non-senescent gene-->
      <li>VacuumResistance_Total</li> <!--breathless gene, requires odyssey-->
      <li>PaccaMechManMechanitorBandwidthArchite</li>
      <!--Ability-->
      <li>PaccaMechManMechShutdown</li>
      <li>PaccaMechManMechLink</li>
      <li>PaccaMechManMechSummon</li>
      <!--Psychics-->
      <li>PsychicAbility_Enhanced</li>
      <!--Movement-->
      <li>MoveSpeed_Slow</li>
      <!--Mood-->
      <li>PaccaMechManBoredomResistant</li>
      <li>PaccaMechManMechHiveConnection</li>
      <!--Temperature-->
      <li>MinTemp_LargeDecrease</li> <!--Cold Super tolerant-->
      <!--Resist and Sensitive-->
      <li>ToxResist_Total</li>
      <li>UVSensitivity_Mild</li>
      <!--Violence-->
      <li>Aggression_HyperAggressive</li>
      <li>MeleeDamage_Weak</li>
      <!--Sleep-->
      <li>Sleepy</li>
      <!--Pain-->
      <li>Pain_Reduced</li>
      <!--Cosmetic-->
      <li>Eyes_Red</li>
      <!--Skin-->
      <li>PaccaMechManSkin_MechGreenishWhite</li>
      <!--Misc-->
      <li>Learning_Fast</li>
      <li>CaveDweller</li>
      <li>PaccaMechManPlasteelArmor</li>
      <li>PaccaMechManTechWoven</li>
      <li>PaccaMechManCerebrexHead</li>
      <!--Skills-->
      <li>AptitudeTerrible_Melee</li>
      <li>AptitudeRemarkable_Construction</li>
      <li>AptitudeTerrible_Cooking</li>
      <li>AptitudeTerrible_Animals</li>
      <li>AptitudeRemarkable_Crafting</li>
      <li>AptitudeRemarkable_Intellectual</li>
    </genes>
  </XenotypeDef>

  <XenotypeDef>
    <defName>PaccaMechMan_ScytheMan</defName>
    <label>Scythman</label>
    <description>Scythmen are heavily specialized killing machines. While they lack the titular Scythes from their forebearers, the Scythers, Scythmen are still incredibly adept at chasing down enemies and defeating them in melee combat. However, they struggle when handling ranged weapons, and become volatile if they don't get the opportunity to kill for too long. They are also weak to EMPs.</description>
    <descriptionShort>Scythmen are fast and great in melee combat, but struggle to use ranged weapons, and become moody and volatile if they don't kill often enough. They are also weak to EMPs.</descriptionShort>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Xenotypes/Dirtmole</iconPath>
